### **CSS Styling**
You can create separate CSS files for each component (e.g., `Navbar.css`, `Hero.css`, etc.) or use a CSS-in-JS solution like `styled-components`. Hereâ€™s an example of global styles in `App.css`:

```css
/* src/styles/App.css */
body {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  line-height: 1.6;
}

.container {
  max-width: 1200px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 20px;
}

h1, h2, h3 {
  color: #007bff;
}

.btn {
  background: #007bff;
  color: #fff;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  text-decoration: none;
  border-radius: 5px;
  display: inline-block;
  margin-top: 10px;
}

.btn:hover {
  background: #0056b3;
}
```

